# Central support age PUBLIC key — the operator's fleet recovery key.
#
# Generate ONCE on your support machine:
#     age-keygen -o ~/.config/farmpos/support_age.key
# It prints "Public key: age1....". Put ONLY that public line into a file named
# support_age.pub (drop the .example suffix) next to this one, e.g.:
#     age1qz9examplepublickeystringxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# register-store.sh copies support_age.pub into each box's secrets/ so backup.sh
# encrypts every backup to BOTH the store's key AND this one. That lets you restore
# or reproduce ANY store's backup with the single support PRIVATE key — which must
# live ONLY on your support machine / password manager, NEVER in this repo.
#
# The public key here is safe to commit (public keys cannot decrypt anything).
